{"id":"h_mr5k39hu_ww0o","text":"When the user says \"ascii galaxy\", \"the void\", or \"/void\" (formerly \"/galaxy\") they mean the pi TUI landing-page extension ~/.pi/agent/extensions/void-blackhole.ts, not the ~/Developer/galaxy website (which is the lensed-blackhole personal site).","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"correction","created":"2026-07-03T23:20:08.658Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-03T23:20:08.658Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false}
{"id":"h_mr5l245j_gcds9p3m","text":"When spawning pi programmatically (RPC/print/json mode) for tests, pass --write, because the read-only-default extension disables edit/write tools in every new session.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"environment","created":"2026-07-03T23:47:14.694Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-03T23:47:14.694Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false}
{"id":"h_mr5lmluz_jv9hxdhc","text":"When a subagent reports file state that conflicts with the lead's earlier read, re-verify the actual file content directly before ruling — files can change mid-session and the lead's memory of a file goes stale.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"orchestration","created":"2026-07-04T00:03:10.763Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T00:03:10.763Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false}
{"id":"h_mr5og2re_bwmlp7tk","text":"When resizing WORDMARK or other fixed-width art in a pi setHeader render, update every width guard to measure the art (max line length) — hardcoded thresholds cause TUI uncaughtException crashes when a rendered line exceeds terminal width.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"gotcha","created":"2026-07-04T01:22:04.922Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T01:22:04.922Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr5p7pws_jw73u37k","text":"If request_write_mode reports \"not found\" but exists in the extension file on disk, the pi process loaded a stale copy (extensions load at session start) — dispatch the subagent call anyway, since the write-gate's subagent tool_call hook still pops the UI menu to switch to write mode; never fall back to asking in prose.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"orchestration","created":"2026-07-04T01:43:34.635Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T01:43:34.635Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr5q6prq_ypqh1hf8","text":"Pi's TUI stacks header + chat + custom component + footer into one buffer and pins the viewport to the bottom N terminal rows, so a full-screen landing component must keep the header at zero rows while it owns the screen (install tall headers only after the component closes) — reserve tweaks inside the component cannot compensate for header lines above it.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"gotcha","created":"2026-07-04T02:10:47.413Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T02:10:47.413Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr5t3f3y_86jv0cg9","text":"To run the void-blackhole extension's TS harness, use `node --experimental-strip-types --experimental-transform-types _void_harness.mts args...` instead of `npx tsx`, because tsx's CJS interop hook throws ERR_PACKAGE_PATH_NOT_EXPORTED on the pure-ESM @earendil-works/pi-coding-agent package.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"environment","created":"2026-07-04T03:32:12.478Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T03:32:12.478Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"reproduced"}
{"id":"h_mr5upxvw_doe8069e","text":"When the user says \"status bar\" about pi's TUI, they mean the prompt input/editor bar (the box you type in), not the footer line.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"correction","created":"2026-07-04T04:17:42.860Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T04:17:42.860Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"user-confirmed"}
{"id":"h_mr5uv3so_n918xniy","text":"At ~500-line single-session scope, prefer a strong model over deeper orchestration: the benchmark passed all tests across configs, but fable-solo ranked above the full pipeline at about half the cost while Sonnet had spec-corner defects.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"orchestration","created":"2026-07-04T04:21:43.800Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T04:21:43.800Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"reproduced"}
{"id":"h_mr5vqdg7_wr9g26tr","text":"When a pi extension reports \"shortcut conflicts with built-in, skipping\", check ~/.pi/agent/keybindings.json first — a user rebinding of a built-in action to that key causes the conflict, and removing the rebind (reverting to the action's default key) is the fix rather than changing the extension's shortcut.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"gotcha","created":"2026-07-04T04:46:02.647Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T04:46:02.647Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr64pqxy_nbkhmgko","text":"When the user gives a list of tasks or multiple distinct tasks in one message, use the task tool (add/list/toggle) to track them instead of just replying inline.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"workflow","created":"2026-07-04T08:57:30.021Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T08:57:30.021Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"user-confirmed"}
{"id":"h_mr5udd6q_vukgl5n0","text":"Before re-fixing a bug already described in the heuristics store, check recent session logs — a prior fix may have been reverted by a later \"undo all changes\" request, silently reintroducing the same bug.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"gotcha","created":"2026-07-04T04:07:56.162Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T04:07:56.162Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr5ut2oy_vzdtkqwq","text":"In pi TUI setHeader components, always truncateToWidth() every returned line even when a width guard already exists — a stale/raced width param can bypass the guard and overflow the terminal, crashing the TUI; the width guard alone is not sufficient.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"gotcha","created":"2026-07-04T04:20:09.058Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T04:20:09.058Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr5vsr40_uh1emf8q","text":"Pi's startup [Skills]/[Prompts]/[Extensions]/[Themes] sections are rendered by showLoadedResources() in dist/modes/interactive/interactive-mode.js via addLoadedSection() calls — to hide a specific section, comment out just that section's addLoadedSection call (keeps others and Context/diagnostics intact); re-apply after any pi package reinstall/update since dist/ is regenerated.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"environment","created":"2026-07-04T04:47:53.663Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T04:47:53.663Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr68t102_vb7xdz22","text":"When testing git-commit gating in ~/.pi/agent, the launchd autocommit daemon is WatchPath-triggered on the whole dir (settings.json/keybindings.json/AGENTS.md) and commits any file edit within ~10s — so test the pre-commit hook by invoking .pi-vcs/hooks/pre-commit directly with the file staged (race-immune) rather than via `git commit`, which the daemon will sweep mid-block.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"environment","created":"2026-07-04T10:52:01.489Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T10:52:01.489Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr69pwqg_7jr2bquc","text":"When modifying pi message-queue behavior, preserve native Enter-to-send-or-steer and Option+Enter-to-queue-follow-up unless explicitly asked otherwise.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"workflow","created":"2026-07-04T11:17:35.607Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T11:17:35.607Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"user-confirmed"}
{"id":"h_mr6a1h0g_74czw8bh","text":"The graphify `query` action anchors lexically on literal tokens in the question (a vague word like \"result\" BFS-walks unrelated variables), so use `explain` with a concrete node name or phrase queries around distinctive identifiers.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"gotcha","created":"2026-07-04T11:26:35.104Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T11:26:35.104Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr6ayaby_dz6c8ifn","text":"In pi 0.80.3, extensions cannot programmatically dispatch slash commands: sendUserMessage() hard-sets expandPromptTemplates:false so \"/cmd\" text goes to the LLM verbatim, and ctx.reload() exists only on command contexts — auto-reload from event hooks is infeasible despite the extensions.md reload_runtime example suggesting otherwise.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"gotcha","created":"2026-07-04T11:52:06.094Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T11:52:06.094Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr6bnodv_yqcda4ez","text":"The pi graph tool (graphify-bridge) resolves graphify-out by walking up from cwd with a fallback to the agent config dir's graph — a cwd with its own graphify-out always wins, so from unrelated directories graph answers describe the ~/.pi/agent config, not the local project.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"gotcha","created":"2026-07-04T12:11:50.707Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T12:11:50.707Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr6ct77f_srg5s8ny","text":"After editing loaded resources (extensions, skills, prompts, themes, AGENTS.md) in ~/.pi/agent, run /refresh (or /reload) so pi picks up the changes instead of running on a stale in-memory copy.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"workflow","created":"2026-07-04T12:44:07.995Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T12:44:07.995Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"user-confirmed"}
{"id":"h_mr6dj5qf_yjq91q97","text":"When QA'ing pi extensions, have the QA subagent live-fire them in its own session — extensions load in spawned subagent sessions too, so the dispatch itself becomes the integration test (a graph-first block was observed live in-run this way).","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"orchestration","created":"2026-07-04T13:04:19.143Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T13:04:19.143Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr6e8a3u_3dk5o96f","text":"When consecutive peer FAILs converge on the same root cause (e.g. a missing platform hook), stop patching and re-dispatch with an explicitly mandated design re-frame in the task spec — the third round passed only after the dispatch prescribed the session_shutdown-based lifecycle instead of letting the engineer improvise another heartbeat.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"orchestration","created":"2026-07-04T13:23:51.210Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T13:23:51.210Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr6ftver_246fn7ug","text":"When a fix dispatch mandates a repo/vault-wide invariant check (e.g. wikilink resolution), pin the exact checker semantics in the spec — file scope, what counts as a match, code-example exemptions — so implementer and reviewer run the same check; a mismatch here cost a full rework round.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"orchestration","created":"2026-07-04T14:08:38.210Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T14:08:38.210Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr6mm20f_euov280n","text":"When fanning out parallel implementer subagents in one repo, pin disjoint file ownership in each dispatch spec and route all shared-file edits (AGENTS.md, manifests, doc indexes) to a single follow-up worker — verified collision-free in a 3-way fan-out under a live autocommit daemon.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"orchestration","created":"2026-07-04T17:18:30.830Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T17:18:30.830Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr6sqnce_88ngyhbc","text":"In ~/.pi/agent, before graphify doc re-extraction run audit-pipelines.py --full; if uncached docs exist and no Gemini key is set, use the graphify skill LLM path or set a Gemini key, never a bare update.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"gotcha","created":"2026-07-04T20:10:02.797Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T20:10:02.797Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"reproduced"}
{"id":"h_mr6vs8mm_a9189l2d","text":"Always begin any investigation or lookup with the graph tool (query/explain/path) or the oracle wiki before running grep/find or reading files — consult compiled knowledge first, drop to raw search only after.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"workflow","created":"2026-07-04T21:35:15.885Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T21:35:15.885Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"user-confirmed"}
{"id":"h_mr6w2gfb_w4ctlmnz","text":"Keep the orchestration pipeline split so engineers write judgment-bearing code and workers write only fully specified mechanical diffs because a thinker/typist split leaks design decisions into implementation.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"orchestration","created":"2026-07-04T21:43:12.550Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T21:43:12.550Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"user-confirmed"}
{"id":"h_mr6stobv_l29un21n","text":"Never run `graphify --update` in ~/.pi/agent without LLM API keys available to the CLI — it silently degrades to cached-only extraction and wipes the semantic layer for any un-cached docs (the exact mechanism behind the 2026-07-04 giant-component collapse).","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"gotcha","created":"2026-07-04T20:12:24.043Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T20:12:24.043Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr6tqvh2_s7y6ys4n","text":"A from-scratch graphify rebuild of the ~/.pi/agent config corpus with the Gemini-flash backend yields a git-scoped giant-component fraction of ~0.30 vs the curated backup's ~0.66 (near-identical node/edge counts) — flash doesn't reproduce the god-node bridges, so restore the backup rather than regenerate, or rebuild with a denser --backend claude/openai.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"gotcha","created":"2026-07-04T20:38:12.949Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T20:38:12.949Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr6wrke2_3reh8tg6","text":"Always watch for opportunities to update the graph, wiki, code, docs, or canon when work reveals durable knowledge or drift.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"workflow","created":"2026-07-04T22:02:44.089Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T22:02:44.089Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"user-confirmed"}
{"id":"h_mr6wwjum_w1szf8bu","text":"When storing mutable extension state in pi session/tool-result details, deep-clone snapshots on both write and restore so later mutations cannot corrupt historical branch state.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"gotcha","created":"2026-07-04T22:06:36.670Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T22:06:36.670Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"directly-observed"}
{"id":"h_mr6x11dx_cah32as4","text":"When enabling pi auto-write, scope automatic approval to ~/.pi and prompt or block mutations outside that root.","scope":"global","project":null,"category":"correction","created":"2026-07-04T22:10:06.020Z","lastReinforced":"2026-07-04T22:10:06.020Z","hits":0,"source":"agent","pinned":false,"basis":"user-confirmed"}
